caption: This place is not what it used to be, I bought 2 sushi rolls ,both rolls fitted the smallest container you can find , this restaurant is not what it used to be, they don't offer Japanese specialties like they used to , the quality and the quantity is upsetting,  I understand they want to keep it open and it's a family business etc... but they are ripping off people , I used to come to this restaurant when it was opened till 3am on weekends,  the only guy I recognized is the heavy Japanese guy in the kitchen , in the past I saw him poking his nose at work, now he does deliveries! Also the people preparing the food in the kitchen are no longer Japanese.

This place is the most underrated and delicious izakaya in all of NYC.  It’s never crowded, consistently delicious, and has so many things on the menu that I don’t even know where to start.  We come here almost every week.  We’ve never had a bad dish - and this place reminds me of being back in Japan.  I almost don’t want to leave this review because it’s our favorite little spot and we don’t want it to get more crowded but that would be a disservice to this place, especially in Covid times.
Was our favorite restaurant when we lived around the corner. Delicious food, super friendly staff with great service, and they have a great selection of sake. Miss it a lot after having moved away.

In my opinion, this is my neighborhood's treasure. I don't know any other restaurant that has such loyal customers, and deservedly so. They treat you like a mix of royalty and family.  Their menu accommodates those seeking comfort food, old favorites, and new taste adventures alike. They have a large regular menu and changing specials menu. You'll find dishes that you've never had before and the ones that you have had elsewhere are better executed as well as carefully & beautifully presented here.  All of their house specialties are amazing. My favorite is the eel prepared by the chef and owner. The best eel I've ever had.  They also have a well curated sake & shochu list.
Authentic Japanese food from a family-run  business. I love this place. I hope they can survive.
The sushi and sashimi weren’t fresh at all. Way too pricy for what it was. Not going back
I love this place and hope it survives this crazy time.
